{
"content_id": "313371",
"reference_id": 109055,
"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "彼得前書 5:1–5",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "60005001-60005005",
"language": "zht",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>彼得形容<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108118\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">教會長老</span>和領袖是神子民的<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108278\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">牧羊人</span>。他對他們的教導就像耶穌在路加福音22:24–30中對祂的<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108040\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">門徒</span>的教導。教會領袖不可驕傲或像統治者一樣行事。耶穌是大牧人，他們必須順服祂。他們必須效法耶穌<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108059\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">事奉的領袖</span>的榜樣。忠心服事的領袖將在耶穌回到地上時分享祂的榮耀。其他信徒必須尊重和跟隨像耶穌一樣帶領的領袖。</p>",
